SALMONELLOSIS, SEROTYPE TYPHIMURIUM - FRANCE: LAMB AND MUTTON
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 25 Oct 2018
From: Maria Pardos de la Gandara <maria.pardos-de-la-gandara@pasteur.fr> [edited]


We have had [laboratory confirmation] of a _Salmonella_ Typhimurium outbreak in France. It was a small, localized outbreak related to lamb and mutton that occurred in one region in France, with a local source of contamination.

There was no link with the UK ongoing outbreak. The comparison of strains has shown no relatedness between UK strains and French strains. The French outbreak is now over.

--
Maria Pardos de la Gandara MD PhD
Directrice adjointe du CNR E. coli, Shigella et Salmonella
Unite de recherche et d'expertise des Bacteries Pathogenes Enteriques
Paris, France
